## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Staff Account Creation Approach** — Two options:
> 
> **Option A (Simple):** Admin creates staff profile in database. Staff signs up themselves through the register page. Admin approves/links them. No Cloud Functions needed.
> 
> **Option B (Full control):** Admin creates the Firebase Auth account directly using a Cloud Function. Requires Firebase Blaze plan (pay-as-you-go, but Cloud Functions free tier = 2M calls/month).
> 
> Which do you prefer?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Staff Password Reset:** When admin edits a staff account and changes password — with Firebase Auth, password changes for other users require either (a) Cloud Functions or (b) sending a password reset email to the staff member. Which approach?

